cardhead649@... writes:


&gt; &quot;Presumptious sort, aren&#39;t you?  Empath, Terrorize!&quot;  The leopard is 
&gt; replaced by the dangerous femme-bot.  &quot;Stay back, or you&#39;ll pay for 
&gt; it.&quot;  Reaching out with her mind, she checks the intentions of the 
&gt; natives.  Not hostile, but prepared nonetheless.
&gt; 
&gt; 

&quot;We mean no harm,&quot; a voice said, but it was unclear if it came from them or 
just one of them. The majority wore strange, tribal like masks. 

Then the one took the mask off. They were indeed humanoid, but with slight 
differences from the humans that would once rule this world. &quot;Come with us,&quot; 
it stated, not entirely moving his mouth... perhaps telepathy of sorts. Then 
he spoke again, motioning with his hand, his accent rather strong, &quot;Koom.... 
koom.&quot; 

The warriors moved towards the pit, as they tossed ropes down to assist the 
whit tiger below. 

As she assisted herself up, & came to ground level.. she looked at the 
humanoids. Then looked at Empath.  Then noticed the one without a mask moving 
away, some of the warriors followed him, that one turned & motioned again for 
them to come. 

She looked at Empath. &quot;May as well,&quot; still in tiger mode, she started to 
follow the unmasked humanoid. This indeed was odd of Maxima.. she knew it... 
but something drove her to go. So much for her plans to the Ark. 


The unmasked one & the warriors led them deep into the forest, then through 
mountains, through a cave, then a steep river valley, with a simple bridge to 
cross that led to a waterfall... behind the waterfall a cave.. through that 
cave & out once more to face a beautiful, stunning land with a breathtaking & 
mighty city. 

&quot;Koom,&quot; the one asked again, as he started to led them towards the city. 

